dcat:Catalog.dc:title: AGRIS Open Data Set - Catalog
dcat:Catalog.dct:rights: Metadata in this catalog can be freely reused. The catalog gives access to a number of interoperable distributions of datasets: each dataset has its own license and usage rights stated in the metadata.
dcat:Catalog.dct:rightsHolder: Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations
dcat:Catalog.dc:creator: Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations
dcat:Catalog.dc:publisher: Food and Agriculture Organization of the United Nations
dcat:Catalog.dc:description: The AGRIS Open Data Set (https://data.apps.fao.org/catalog/dcat/agris) is a collection of datasets extracted from the FAO AGRIS metadata database (https://agris.fao.org/) and made available as XML files using the Dublin Core and the W3C Data Catalog schemas. AGRIS offers this downloadable collection of metadata describing books, journal articles, monographs, book chapters, datasets and grey literature - including unpublished scientific and technical reports, theses, dissertations and conference papers - in the area of food and agriculture in order to facilitate their reuse. While the AGRIS website is open to any individual to search or browse the entire collection, this Open Data Set gives access for machine use to a certain number of metadata records (around 50%), which are the records contributed by AGRIS data providers that agree to share the metadata in an open interoperable format.
dcat:Catalog.dc:subject: agriculture
food security
fisheries
nutrition
forestry
livestock
